Arpe May Join Popolare Milano Management Board, Messori Says

-- B y   T o m m a s o   E b h a r d t   a n d   S o n i a   S i r l e t t i
-- 
2011-10-10T17:52:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-10/arpe-may-join-popolare-milano-management-board-messori-says.html
Former Capitalia SpA Chief Executive
Officer Matteo Arpe may join  Banca Popolare di Milano Scarl (PMI) ’s
management board, said Marcello Messori, a candidate to become
chairman of the bank.  Messori, who leads one of the five lists of candidates for
the new supervisory board that will be elected Oct. 22, said he
contacted Arpe for a role at the bank, according to an e-mailed
statement.  Arpe said he was “available in principle,” Messori said.
Arpe doesn’t own shares in the bank, Messori said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Tommaso Ebhardt at 
